HEADWORD: Tyrolite
<hw>Tyr"o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Tyrol</ets>, where it occurs.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
translucent mineral of a green color and pearly or vitreous luster. It
is a hydrous arseniate of copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

